    OpenDocument-v1.2-os-schema-baseline-HTML-p.txt DETACHED SIGNATURE
    ==================================================================

    This file holds a detached digital signature for the file
    with the same name absent the *.asc suffix.

    SIGNATURE VERIFICATION

    To verify this signature, place both files in a single
    directory.  The files to be checked must not be altered
    in any manner and they should each be downloaded directly
    from their source on the web.

    If the file to be checked has been renamed, rename this
    signature file to match, with the addition of the .asc
    suffix.

    To verify the signature using GnuPG, import a copy of the
    OpenPGP Public Key of the signer from <http://keybase.io/orcmid>,
    from <https://people.apache.org/keys/committer/orcmid.asc>,
    or from a PGP Key Server.  The fingerprint of the key is
    04D0 4322 979B 84DE 1077  0334 F96E 89FF D456 628A.

    Verification is by opening a console session in the same
    directory as the pair of files.  Verify the signature by
    simply executing the command

    > gpg n140504f7-OpenDocument-v1.2-os-schema-baseline-HTML-p.txt.asc

    using the name given to this file if it has been renamed.
    For more information on detached-signature verification,
    see <http://nfoworks.org/dev/2014/05/d140502g.htm>.

    Successful verification of the signature establishes that
    the file having this detached signature has not been altered
    since the signing and that the signing was performed using
    the private key corresponding to the public key identified
    in the signature.

    CLAIMS

    File n140504f7-OpenDocument-v1.2-os-schema-baseline-HTML-p.txt
    accessed at <http://nfoworks.org/notes/2014/05/n140504-cache/>
    is ordinary HTML produced from the file n140504f5-OpenDocument-
    v1.2-os-schema-baseline-HTML-prep.txt also provided in the n140504-
    cache. The n140504f7 .txt file is derived from the n140504f5 .txt
    using search and replace operations in a text editor.

    The n140504f6 .txt file is a pre-formatted representation of
    the OpenDocument-v1.2-os-schema.rng file produced by applying
    procedures <http://nfoworks.org/dev/2014/05/d140502e.htm#s6>
    and <http://nfoworks.org/dev/2014/05/d140502e.htm#s7>
    to the n140504f5 .txt file.

    ASSESSMENT OF CLAIMS

    Demonstration of the correspondence between the n140504f7 .txt
    file and OpenDocment-v1.2-os-schema.rng is by demonstration of
    the correspondence between the n140504f7 .txt and the n140504f2
    .prn files.

    In a text editor, add "<html><body><p> at the beginning of the
    n140504f7 .txt file.  Add the line "</p></body></html> after
    the last line of the n140504f7 .txt file.  Save the result as
    a file with .html extension instead of .txt.

    Open the n140504f6 .html file directly in a browser such as
    Internet Explorer 11.  Notice that the page renders properly
    with permalinks at the line numbers and proper formatting of
    a replica of the RNG Schema.  Save the opened browser page as
    a distinct Text File (*.txt) with the name ending in something
    like -p-check.txt.  Also correct any changes made in other
    parts of the file name by the browser.

    This derivative can now be compared with n140504f2 .prn using
    a text DIFF utility.  It is likely that one or more of the
    .prn lines are truncated in the Text File from the browser.
    Confirm that the truncations do not apply in the .html derivative.
    By correcting any lines that deviate in this way from those in
    the .prn file, the derivative Text File should also verify with
    the detached signature of the n140504f2 .prn.


